The article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the House and Senate leadership, as well as the chairmen and ranking members of the House and Senate committees. The letter is in response to section 1117 of the Supplemental Appropriations Act, 2009, and it provides a report related to Afghanistan and Pakistan. This is the fourth report submitted under section 1117 and covers the period from January 1, 2011, through June 30, 2011, with some assessment through August 31, 2011. The letter acknowledges progress in the fight against al-Qa'ida and the reversal of Taliban's momentum in Afghanistan. It also mentions progress in training the Afghan National Security Forces and the plan to recover the 33,000 U.S. troop surge announced in December 2009. The letter emphasizes that further modifications or adjustments to the strategy are not required at this time, but acknowledges that challenges remain. President Obama underscores the importance of successfully implementing the policy in Afghanistan and Pakistan.